    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While your instinct to manage your injury on your own is understandable, I must emphasize that relying on home treatment without professional evaluation, especially for someone who has sustained a fall, is risky. Pain and swelling can persist for several days or even weeks after the incident, and it's still possible for a fracture not to be immediately apparent in an X-ray. Delaying professional assessment could complicate your condition and lead to complications including but not limited to impaired mobility, chronic pain, and arthritis. Make an effort to arrange a convenient clinic visit, as your immediate care takes priority, and could save you considerable discomfort later. Health professionals can also provide advice on effective home care techniques if they're monitoring your recovery pace, ensuring you're coping with the injury appropriately in the meantime. It's always better to err on the side of caution concerning bone injuries; your health is worth the extra effort and planning now.",
